<h1>Flickr integration</h1>
<p>Users can:
  <ul>
    <li>Import files from Flickr</li>
    <li>Publish photos and videos to Flickr</li>
  </ul>
</p>



<h2>Link Flickr account with VisualREST</h2>
<p>
  Authorization to user's Flickr account has three steps:
  <ul>
    <li>Go to: http://visualrest.cs.tut.fi/user/{username}/flickr_authorization <br />(or Settings->Flickr->Authorize)</li>
    <li>User is directed to Flickr website for authorizing access to the Flickr account</li>
    <li>Flickr access token is stored in VisualREST</li>
  </ul>
</p>



<br /><br />

<h2>Import content from Flickr</h2>
<p>
  To import content from Flickr you need to have a virtual container and follow these instructions:
  <ul>
    <li>Select virtual container from list.</li>
    <li>Select public/private photos to import from Flickr.</li>
    <li>Press 'Import photos from Flickr'.</li>
  </ul>
</p>




<br /><br />

<h2>Publish photo or video to Flickr</h2>
<p>
  Photos and videos can be published to Flickr using <b>HTTP request</b> or <b>using the form in 'settings->Flickr->Publish photo to Flickr'</b> 
  or <b>in file search using the Flickr-logo.</b>
</p>

<h3>HTTP request</h3>
  <li><b>method:</b>     POST</li>
  <li><b>url:</b>        http://visualrest.cs.tut.fi/user/{username}/flickrPublishPhoto</li>
  <li><b>parameters:</b></li> 
  <ul>
    <li>authentication ( i_am_client, auth_username, auth_timestamp, auth_hash )</li>
    <li><b>file_uri</b>: uri to the file in VisualREST
  </ul>
</ul>
<p>
  <b>CURL example:</b><br />
  curl -X POST http://visualrest.cs.tut.fi/user/heikki/flickrPublishPhoto -F file_uri=http://visualrest.cs.tut.fi/user/heikki/device/dev20111208/files/bus.jpg 
  -F auth_username=heikki -F auth_timestamp=12344334 -F auth_hash=XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX 
  -F i_am_client=true  
</p>



<br /><br />

<h2>Test Flickr access token</h2>
<p>
  Access token to Flickr can be tested, to make sure it is valid.
</p>

<h3>HTTP request</h3>
  <li><b>method:</b>     GET</li>
  <li><b>url:</b>        http://visualrest.cs.tut.fi/user/{username}/flickrConnected</li>
  <li><b>parameters:</b></li> 
  <ul>
    <li>authentication ( i_am_client, auth_username, auth_timestamp, auth_hash )</li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<p>
  <b>CURL example:</b><br />
  curl -X GET http://visualrest.cs.tut.fi/user/heikki/flickrConnected
  -F auth_username=heikki -F auth_timestamp=12344334 -F auth_hash=XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX 
  -F i_am_client=true  
</p>



